        <updateDate>2021-07-08T17:14:18Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Kathryn Manginelli Act of 2021 or the Compassionate Retirement Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill allows premature distributions, without penalty, from tax-exempt retirement plans that are made to an individual who is certified by a physician as terminally ill. It also modifies the definition of <em>terminally ill individual</em> to increase from 24 to 84 the number of months after certification that an individual's illness can reasonably be expected to result in death.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
